  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But I never met him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But she-- she was the go-between.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it-- it-- on and on to-- to other.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It's a long-- a long story.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So all-- all in my book.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I hope people will-- will read it-- read the story And finally, when I get-- I got a promise of what we wanted.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We wanted a-- a landing ground in-- in Hungary for British parachutists to come in-- to come in.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And it was in collaboration with the Soviet Union, that the Soviet armies were pushing the-- the-- the German army.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And then, this operation was planned to-- to attack and stab the German army in the back.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So that was my-- my assignment, to find a landing ground for parachutists, commandos, and in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they found one-- Count [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I don't know if-- if the name rings to you.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then, oh well, at least I had that much.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Otherwise, it was a failure, because it was every-- everything [NON-ENGLISH] and the-- the air was [NON-ENGLISH] filled.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then-- and then, I had to make a decision.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Well, she advised me to-- to get somebody, that she has a-- a trusted young man who could take my message back to-- back to Slovakia, to my mission, because there were four of us.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But the general could arranged it for-- it was impossible to get.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I was the-- I was the main one, the-- the leading person of it, because I knew most around [INAUDIBLE] to-- and then-- then, I decided it-- it can't be done, because I can't track it down.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Can't-- and just too delayed, everything in one-- well, it's-- it's impossible, because I have to read the whole situation there and what are-- what are the possibilities for the-- for the mission.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
